        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "## Citric Acid pKa Values (SRD-46)\n\nCitric acid is a **triprotic acid (H₃L)** with three successive deprotonation steps:\n\n| Step | Equilibrium | pKa | Temperature (°C) | Ionic Strength (M) |\n|------|-------------|-----|-------------------|--------------------|\n| pKa₁ | H₃L ⇌ H₂L⁻ + H⁺ | **2.90** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| pKa₂ | H₂L⁻ ⇌ HL²⁻ + H⁺ | **4.35** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| pKa₃ | HL²⁻ ⇌ L³⁻ + H⁺ | **5.65** | 25 | 0.1 |\n\n> All values measured at **25 °C**, ionic strength **I = 0.1 M** (aqueous solution).  \n> Source: NIST SRD-46 (VLM IDs: vlm_157473, vlm_157459, vlm_157439)",
